Sentencas: The performance and stability of La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta-electrolyte supported solid oxide fuel cells with composite LaSr2Fe2CrO9-delta-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2 anodes were studied in wet H-2 and coal syngas containing phosphine impurity.
Titulo: Degradation of LaSr2Fe2CrO9-δ solid oxide fuel cell anodes in phosphine-containing fuels

Sentencas: Introduction of 5-20 ppm PH3 into the fuels caused an initial slow cell performance degradation followed by a very rapid complete cell degradation that initiated within 11-24 h - earlier at higher PH3 concentration.
Titulo: Degradation of LaSr2Fe2CrO9-δ solid oxide fuel cell anodes in phosphine-containing fuels

Sentencas: There was no recovery after removing PH3 impurity from the fuels.
Titulo: Degradation of LaSr2Fe2CrO9-δ solid oxide fuel cell anodes in phosphine-containing fuels

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance analysis suggested that the initial gradual performance degradation was due to conductivity loss of the oxide anode due to chemisorption and reaction of phosphine.
Titulo: Degradation of LaSr2Fe2CrO9-δ solid oxide fuel cell anodes in phosphine-containing fuels

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction analysis showed the formation of FePx and LaPO4 compounds.
Titulo: Degradation of LaSr2Fe2CrO9-δ solid oxide fuel cell anodes in phosphine-containing fuels

Sentencas: The rapid degradation presumably occurred when most or all of the Fe initially present in the LaSr2Fe2CrO9-delta was consumed.
Titulo: Degradation of LaSr2Fe2CrO9-δ solid oxide fuel cell anodes in phosphine-containing fuels

Sentencas: Thermodynamic calculations confirmed that Fe is highly reactive with PH3 at 800 degrees C, even at concentrations below 1 ppm (C) 2010
Titulo: Degradation of LaSr2Fe2CrO9-δ solid oxide fuel cell anodes in phosphine-containing fuels
